  m_Name: Step6_DrivenGear
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::EngineNarrationStep
  stepLabel: DRIVEN GEAR
  narrationText: "Finally \u2014 the driven gear and output axle.\n\nThis receives
    the rotation from the crankshaft and transfers it outward to the rest of the
    drivetrain \u2014 eventually reaching the differential then the wheels.\n\nIn
    the real Porsche 911, the engine sends power rearward through a transaxle. In
    this model, you can see exactly how that transfer begins."
  voiceOver: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 1ee0a98a89296fd4888bdfd8e78d5fd9, type: 3}
